\par\pard\plain \tx0\li360\fi360\sa120\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf7 Sarah regretted breaking her promise to Evan and working after she arrived at Liz's place. Despite the option of completing the trip without a word, facing no consequences, her strong moral compass compelled her to confess to Evan. Liz consoled Sarah and assured her that she was already embraced as a part of the family.<!$Scr_Ps::4>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\fi360\ltrch\loch \f0\fs18\b0\i0
\par\pard\plain \tx0\ltrch\loch {\f3\fs22\b1\i0\cf6 <$Scr_Ps::3>Leading Context:<!$Scr_Ps::3><$Scr_Ps::4>}
\par\pard\plain \tx0\li360\fi360\sa120\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs22\b0\i0\cf7 Earlier in the chapter, Sarah had played a mental tug-of-war between her workaholic nature and her promise to Evan that she would not work during this trip. Initially it look like the work addict had won the battle. However, by the end of the scene Sarah felt pathetic failure of low integrity. This scene picks up after she decided to turn off her phone and put it in her purse where she wouldn't be tempted to look at it.<!$Scr_Ps::4>}
